(firstQuint)The Impact of Problem-Based Learning (PBL) and Lecturing.

 A total of 40 second-year nursing students participated: 20 students in the PBL group and 20 students in the traditional lecture (control) group.

 The students underwent a one-semester course using the two methods of education.

 The Impact of Problem-Based Learning (PBL) and Lecturing@highlight

The present study aimed to compare the effect of education through problem-based learning (PBL) or lectures on behavior, attitude and learning of nursing students.

